1) Quantitative Analysis:
Participants struggled to identify safety-critical flaws. Our
analysis includes all flaws identified by participants and authors. Many were flagged by only one participant (Figure 3),
and none were consistently detected; some safety-critical issues were missed entirely by all participants.
Participants demonstrated the ability to identify flaws
involving technical information. Of the 79 total flaws identified across all participants, 72.2% involved technical content,
33.3% involved domain-specific content, and 40.7% could be
identified without technical or domain expertise. Although detection was inconsistent, participants demonstrated the ability
to critically assess technical information despite their limited

